{"TopicId":222108,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Expanded Colour Editor","CreatedByName":"Infinite Aerospace","CreatedById":230192,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-26T13:45:29Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Infinite Aerospace","CreatedById":230192,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-26T13:45:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, I love the colour editor\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Ehowever\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Ein my opinion there\u0027s still a fair bit of improvement in terms of functionality\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eand\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0 in terms of quality of life.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) There\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Eneeds\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0to be more options to \u0027lock in\u0027 colour combinations, to have a set of presets rather than just the singular \u0027Agency Colours\u0027. This would be a great addition for anyone who has an overarching theme to their designs. So when a user makes a colour combination they like, they can save it to \u0027Preset 1\u0027 for example.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) There should be a drop down menu that allows the user to pick various shader types, for example Metallic for example, either that or have preset material types. I don\u0027t mind the vibrant \u0027plastic\u0027 look of stock KSP2 but I think it\u0027d be great to cater for those who want to keep a bit more realism to their builds.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jeq","CreatedById":172375,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-26T14:00:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor this i would like parts remember last color used for them at current savegame. For example most of time i would like to have boosters be different from other rocket, to do this for every vessel and every part is time consuming.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd when changing one color preset it would maybe change current design of rocket using that preset.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently there is possible to make metallic colour but only if lose some color and allow metal shine behind it, colors are maybe plastic when used solid colors but it might suite Kerbal world and rockets look like they are toys.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-26T14:23:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224352216\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703598329\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022230192\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Infinite Aerospace\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n36 minutes ago, Infinite Aerospace said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Eneeds\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0to be more options to \u0027lock in\u0027 colour combinations\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a mod for that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022161422\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9375142963\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/214821-color-presets/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Infinite Aerospace","CreatedById":230192,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-26T20:08:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224352230\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222108\u0022 d